entry.title: App Service: Use common proxy setup for almost all AppServiceProxy tests
entry.content:
Tests in AppServiceProxyTest were responsible for creating their own

Profile and AppServiceProxy, which led to a variety of different ways of

setting up the test.



In particular, some tests initialized AppServiceProxy with a null

Profile, and didn't run Initialize, which is a state that can't happen

in production. This resulted in fields being unexpectedly null, like

ShortcutRegistryCache() in shortcut tests.



Instead, this CL adds a common TestingProfile and Proxy definition to

the test fixture, which ensures a consistent setup across tests.

entry.content:
This CL fixes nacl_helper method to append command line arguments.



CommandLine::InitFromArgv considers the first string in vector as a

program path instead of the command line option even if the command line

object was initialized with NO_PROGRAM.

CommandLine::AppendArguments skips program path to append when

include_program is set to false, so the current implementation

unintentionally drops the first string in the current command line.

entry.title: Fix the broken tests when AppStorage is enabled(Part 24).
entry.content:
When the AppStorage feature is enabled, AppService blocks the app

publishing until it's ready, after reading from the AppStorage file.

This may break some tests, e.g. AutotestPrivateApiTest.AutotestPrivate.



Because Chrome browser is added to the shelf at a very early stage,

when the Chrome browser app hasn't been added to AppRegistryCache in

AppService. So IsAppPinEditable returns false[1], and

pin_state_forced_by_type = true. This result is different when the

AppStorage feature is disabled, so the test reports error.



Actually, when the Chrome browser is added to the shelf, it is not as

an App, so it won't have the pin/unpin in menu[2]. So we can add a

similar checking for that as well, if the shelf item is not an app

type, don't call IsAppPinEditable to get `pin_state_forced_by_type`.



[1] https://source.chromium.org/chromium/chromium/src/+/main:chrome/browser/ui/ash/shelf/chrome_shelf_controller_util.cc;l=187;drc=67d90538f11c6b232dbfd716075db52aeb34fd15?q=IsAppPinEditable&ss=chromium%2Fchromium%2Fsrc



[2] https://source.chromium.org/chromium/chromium/src/+/main:chrome/browser/ui/ash/shelf/shelf_context_menu.cc;l=140



BUG=1385932, b:307623506

entry.content:
Instead of placing under the first line of the selection, change the

bounds logic to do the following:

3. If still offscreen, just place at the bottom of the screen.

adjust to keep on screen if needed. (Though it's slightly simplified

now since the vertical positioning logic means we don't need to worry

entry.title: [ForceSignin] Do not finalize profile when attempting to open FRE
entry.content:
When `kForceSigninFlowInProfilePicker` is enabled, and trying to open

the FRE, the result will not open the FRE because of ForceSignin

being enabled, however the profile should not be finalized, since

with the feature flag enabled, the remainder of the flow is still

happening:

- either accepting management, or

- sync confirmation screen

and both of them are happening in the profile picker before the

opening of a browser (before finalising the profile).

entry.content:
For passkeys, we'll want to know whether the hw_protected security

domain is:

a) empty

b) non-empty, with a usable virtual device. (This will always

be an Android LSKF for now.)

c) non-empty, but with no usable virtual devices.



To support this, the `DownloadAuthenticationFactorsRegistrationState`

method on `TrustedVaultConnection` reports this information.
